<?xpacket end=\'r\'?>bi\0\0\0\0IENDB`',1,'This is a simple Spring MVC tutorial showing how to set up a Spring MVC project..											\r\n												\r\n												'),(17,26,0,' Interface and Abstract Class','2020-05-27 18:16:33','<h4><strong>Difference Between Interface and Abstract Class</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<ul new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: \" times=\"\">\r\n	<li>Tea\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Interface : Interface can have only abstract methods</li>\r\n		<li>Abstract : Abstract class can have abstract and non-abstract methods.(From Java 8, it can have default and static methods also)</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>variables\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Interface : Variables declared only static and final variables</li>\r\n		<li>Abstract : Variables declared final, non-final, static and non-static variables</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Apply\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Interface : Java interface should be implemented using keyword &ldquo;implements&rdquo;</li>\r\n		<li>Abstract : A Java abstract class should be extended using keyword &ldquo;extends&rdquo;</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Extend\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Interface : An interface can extend another Java interface only</li>\r\n		<li>Abstract : An abstract class can extend another Java class and implement multiple Java interfaces.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Implementation\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Interface : Interface can&rsquo;t provide the implementation of abstract class.</li>\r\n		<li>Abstract : Abstract class can provide the implementation of interface</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Accessibility of Data Members\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Interface : Members of a Java interface are public by default.</li>\r\n		<li>Abstract : A Java abstract class can have class members like private, protected, etc.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: \" times=\"\">.Interface is absolutely abstract and cannot be instantiated; A Java abstract class also cannot be instantiated, but can be invoked if a main() exists. 8.In comparison with java abstract classes, java interfaces are slow as it requires extra indirection.</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"code-block\" style=\"margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; display: flex; flex-direction: row; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\">\r\n<div class=\"code-container\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; flex: 1 1 0%; min-width: 0px; overflow-y: hidden; width: 600.438px;\">\r\n<div class=\"syntaxhighlighter nogutter  \" id=\"highlighter_98903\" style=\"padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; width: 600.438px; margin: 1em 0px !important; font-size: 1em !important; position: relative !important; overflow: auto !important;\">\r\n<table bitstream=\"\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" mono=\"\" sans=\"\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; border-spacing: 0px; width: 600px; margin: 0px !important; padding: 0px !important; border: 0px !important; font-size: 0.99em !important; vertical-align: baseline !important; text-align: left !important; line-height: 1.2em !important; border-radius: 0px !important; background: none !important; bottom: auto !important; float: none !important; height: auto !important; left: auto !important; outline: 0px !important; overflow: hidden !important; position: static !important; right: auto !important; top: auto !important; box-sizing: content-box !important; font-family: Consolas, \" vera=\"\">\r\n	<tbody style=\"margin: 0px !important; padding: 0px !important; border: 0px !important; font-size: 0.99em !important; vertical-align: baseline !important; border-radius: 0px !important; background: none !important; bottom: auto !important; float: none !important; height: auto !important; left: auto !important; line-height: 1.2em !important; outline